@startuml C4_Future_AIIntegration
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Future Vision - AI/ML Integration

Boundary(ai_layer, "AI/ML Layer") {
    Component(ml_pipeline, "MLPipeline", "Training", "Model development")
    Component(feature_eng, "FeatureEngineering", "Prep", "Extract features")
    Component(model_training, "ModelTraining", "ML", "Train models")
    Component(model_evaluation, "ModelEvaluation", "Validation", "Evaluate accuracy")
}

Boundary(inference, "Inference & Serving") {
    Component(model_serving, "ModelServing", "API", "Inference server")
    Component(ml_monitoring, "MLMonitoring", "Ops", "Model drift detection")
    Component(model_versioning, "ModelVersioning", "Release", "Model versions")
}

Boundary(use_cases, "AI-Powered Use Cases") {
    Component(resource_optimization, "ResourceOptimization", "ML", "Predict best resource allocation")
    Component(anomaly_detection, "AnomalyDetection", "ML", "Detect workflow anomalies")
    Component(predictive_sla, "PredictiveSLA", "ML", "Forecast SLA violations")
    Component(workflow_generation, "WorkflowGeneration", "GenAI", "Auto-generate workflows from specs")
}

Boundary(feedback_loop, "Feedback Loop") {
    Component(prediction_eval, "PredictionEvaluation", "Validation", "Evaluate predictions")
    Component(retraining, "Retraining", "Improvement", "Retrain with new data")
    Component(deployment, "Deployment", "Release", "Deploy improved model")
}

ml_pipeline --> feature_eng: Prepares data
feature_eng --> model_training: Feeds to
model_training --> model_evaluation: Validates
model_evaluation --> model_serving: If approved
model_serving --> ml_monitoring: Monitors

model_serving --> resource_optimization: Predicts allocation
model_serving --> anomaly_detection: Detects anomalies
model_serving --> predictive_sla: Forecasts violations

prediction_eval --> retraining: If accuracy drops
retraining --> deployment: Redeploys

Note as N1
YAWL AI/ML Vision (2026-2027):

Resource Optimization (ML):
- Predict optimal resource allocation
- Learn from historical allocations
- Suggest assignments before human
- Continuous improvement

Anomaly Detection (ML):
- Detect unusual workflow patterns
- Predict failures before they happen
- Reduce MTTR by early warning
- Improve reliability

Predictive SLA (ML):
- Forecast SLA violations hours ahead
- Allow proactive intervention
- Improve service levels
- Reduce customer impact

Workflow Generation (GenAI):
- Spec: "Approval workflow for expenses <$1000"
- GenAI generates YAWL net definition
- Human review + refinement
- Deploy immediately
- 10× faster workflow creation

Feedback Loop:
1. Make prediction (resource allocation)
2. Measure outcome (task completion time)
3. Evaluate accuracy
4. Retrain if accuracy drops
5. Deploy improved model
6. Repeat

Requirements:
- Historical data (12+ months)
- Feedback loop (outcome measurement)
- Model versioning (track performance)
- Human-in-the-loop (review before action)
- Explainability (understand predictions)

Timeline:
- Q3 2026: Resource optimization MVP
- Q4 2026: Anomaly detection + predictive SLA
- Q1 2027: Workflow generation
- Q2 2027: Multi-tenant model isolation
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
